Data from PhosphositePlus is marked with a source column of 'psp'. PhosphositePlus license applies to this data.
PSP is licensed by Cell Signaling Technology (CST) for non-commercial use under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License. Warning: PSP data is not for commerical use. Refer to PSP's license information on https://www.phosphosite.org/staticDownloads for additional information. 

2. Libraries - BL-KA, BL-stKSMoyKA include data from Kinome Atlas.
If you use this library, you must reference their work as instructed in the below source articles.
Johnson, J. L., Yaron, T. M., Huntsman, E. M., Kerelsky, A., Song, J., Regev, A., Lin, T. Y., Liberatore, K., Cizin, D. M., Cohen, B. M., Vasan, N., Ma, Y., Krismer, K., Robles, J. T., van de Kooij, B., van Vlimmeren, A. E., Andrée-Busch, N., Käufer, N. F., Dorovkov, M. V., Ryazanov, A. G., … Cantley, L. C. (2023). An atlas of substrate specificities for the human serine/threonine kinome. Nature, 613(7945), 759–766. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-022-05575-3

Yaron-Barir, T. M., Joughin, B. A., Huntsman, E. M., Kerelsky, A., Cizin, D. M., Cohen, B. M., Regev, A., Song, J., Vasan, N., Lin, T. Y., Orozco, J. M., Schoenherr, C., Sagum, C., Bedford, M. T., Wynn, R. M., Tso, S. C., Chuang, D. T., Li, L., Li, S. S., Creixell, P., … Johnson, J. L. (2024). The intrinsic substrate specificity of the human tyrosine kinome. Nature, 629(8014), 1174–1181. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-024-07407-y

3. Library, BL-nKIN includes data from NetworKIN, which was downloaded from KinPred (doi: 10.1371/journal.pcbi.1008681).
If you use this library, you must reference their work as instructed in the below source article.
Xue, B., Jordan, B., Rizvi, S., & Naegle, K. M. (2021). KinPred: A unified and sustainable approach for harnessing proteome-level human kinase-substrate predictions. PLoS computational biology, 17(2), e1008681. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1008681